## v2.1.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1443 "Move `*_state.py` into `state/`" — first
real, verified-local execution of the shim discipline in the SPLIT/move direction.
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Added **Step 8b: Patch-Seam Sweep Across the WHOLE Test Tree** to the SPLIT workflow.
  When you move module X into a subpackage and leave a re-export shim at the old flat path,
  the shim re-exports only X's OWN public symbols — NOT names X imported from elsewhere.
  So `mock.patch("...<old_flat_path>.<imported_name>")` BREAKS for any test that patched a
  name imported INTO X, and those broken seams hide in OTHER test files across the whole tree.
  Step 8b adds the grep command that sweeps every moved module's flat namespace across ALL
  tests and repoints each imported-into name to the canonical `state.<module>` path. This is
  the split-direction analogue of the existing Step C3 (merge-direction repoints).
- Added an explicit note that the `dir(shim)` parity test CANNOT catch an imported-into-name
  patch seam (such names are intentionally absent from the shim), so the grep sweep is a
  SEPARATE, mandatory check.
- Added one new **Failed Attempts** row: "Repoint patch seams only in the moved module's own
  test file" — `test_planner_loop.py` / `test_planner_main.py` patched
  `planner_state.prefetch_issue_states` / `.fetch_all_issue_labels_graphql` (names imported
  INTO the module), 4 failures surfaced only on the first full-suite run.
- Added a **Split-Direction Parameters (#1443)** table under Results & Parameters recording the
  verified-local execution: 3 modules moved into `state/`, explicit `name as name` shims,
  `_review_phase.py` repointed to `from .state import review as review_state`,
  `implementer_phase_runner.py:42,77` left on shim paths (preserves #714 patch surface +
  no-cycle guard), full automation suite 2284 passed, ruff + mypy clean.
- Added a "When to Use" trigger for the imported-into-name patch seam, updated the Overview
  table (Date/Objective/Outcome/Verification) to v2.1.0, extended the Verified Workflow intro
  note to record the executed partial SPLIT, added a `## Verified On` row and a reference for
  #1443.
- Bumped version 2.0.0 → 2.1.0 (MINOR — new findings + a new Failed Attempts row + extended
  workflow; core split/merge recommendation unchanged).

### Why

The approved #1443 plan enumerated patch-seam repoints only in the THREE moved test files plus
one known coupling (`test_implementer_loop.py`). It MISSED `test_planner_loop.py` and
`test_planner_main.py`, which patched names imported INTO `planner_state` from `..github_api`
and `.review`. After the move those bound names live in `hephaestus.automation.state.planner`,
and the flat `planner_state` shim re-exports only `PlannerStateManager` /
`_comments_contain_plan`, so the patch targets vanished → 4 failures that surfaced only on the
first FULL-suite run. The whole-test-tree patch-seam sweep was the decisive fix and is exactly
the step a future split would otherwise re-discover.

### Snapshot reference

Previous version (v2.0.0) full body is preserved in the v2.0.0 entry below (which itself
snapshots v1.0.0). v2.1.0 is a strict superset: it adds Step 8b, one Failed Attempts row, the
Split-Direction Parameters table, and the #1443 Verified On / reference rows without rewriting
any v2.0.0 content.

